gde2-menus
===========

gde2-menus contains the libgde2-menu library, the layout configuration
files for the GDE2 menu, as well as a simple menu editor.

The libgde2-menu library implements the "Desktop Menu Specification"
from freedesktop.org:

  http://freedesktop.org/wiki/Specifications/menu-spec
  http://specifications.freedesktop.org/menu-spec/menu-spec-latest.html

You may download updates to the package from:

   http://pub.gde2-desktop.org/

gde2-menus is a fork of gnome-menus.

Installation
============

If you are not using a released version of gde2-menus (for example, if
you checked out the code from git), you first need to run './autogen.sh'.


How to report bugs
==================

Bugs should be reported to the GDE2 bug tracking system:

   https://github.com/gde2-desktop/gde2-menus/issues

You will need to create an account for yourself.
